## SESSION PROTOCOL

How to run a productive session on this project:

### Opening Steps (do these every time)

1. Read HANDOFF.md first. Do not begin work until you have read and confirmed the full contents.
2. State your task clearly. If you have a prompt file in _docs/, say: "Read _docs/FILENAME.md for the execution spec."
3. Find the bash session path: `ls /sessions/*/mnt/` and set the SITE variable.

### During the Session

4. Use sed via bash for ALL edits to files over 400 lines. Never the Edit tool on large files.
5. Run `tail -5 filename` after every file modification. No exceptions.
6. Run the site-wide truncation verification script before declaring any task complete.
7. Validate all JSON-LD blocks with a Python parse check after schema changes.
8. Update HANDOFF.md at the end of every session with: what changed, which files were modified, updated line counts for any files that grew or shrank.

### Closing Steps

9. Run final site-wide verification.
10. Provide the user with a git commit command summarizing all changes.
11. Update HANDOFF.md session count and "ALL N SESSIONS COMPLETE" line.
12. Verify HANDOFF.md itself is not truncated (`tail -5 HANDOFF.md`).

